ill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The Deregulation Bill does seem to be an opportunity  to preserve our heritage by classifying green lanes as restricted byways, and making Byways Open to All Traffic (BOATS) restricted byways, at least in National Parks and Areas of Natural Beauty.  This would decrease  red tape and litigation, together with the animosity generated when people see the natural environment devastated. There should also be rights of appeal against authorities  which do not take action by issuing Traffic Restriction Orders.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">September 2013</span></p><div style="width:auto; height:21.85pt; float:left;"><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="RAMFooter2"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">2</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">1</span></a></p></div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>